[2026-03-13T19:13:08Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L7Q8736ghtGeweygdvyqX8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Poll Command Implementation Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete understanding of the `cloche poll` command implementation:\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`\n\nThe `cmdPoll` function:\n- Takes a single required argument: `<run-id>`\n- Polls the daemon every 2 seconds indefinitely\n- Prints timestamped progress updates as steps start/complete\n- Monitors container liveness and detects container death after 1 minute\n- Exits with code 0 on success, 1 on failure/cancellation/container death\n- Checks for terminal states: `\"succeeded\"`, `\"failed\"`, `\"cancelled\"`\n- Tracks state changes and new step events to avoid duplicate output\n\nKey variables:\n```go\n- pollInterval := 2 * time.Second\n- containerDeadThreshold := 1 * time.Minute\n- lastStepCount, lastState (for change detection)\n```\n\n### 2. gRPC Service Interface\n**Files:** \n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n\nThe `poll` command uses `GetStatus` RPC:\n- Request: `GetStatusRequest` with `run_id` field\n- Response: `GetStatusResponse` containing:\n  - `run_id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `current_step`\n  - `step_executions` (array of `StepExecutionStatus`)\n  - `error_message`, `container_id`, `container_alive`, `container_dead_since`\n  - `title`, `is_host`\n\n### 3. Domain Types for Run Status\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\nRun state constants:\n```go\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\nTerminal states are: `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\nThe `Run` type includes:\n- `State`, `StepExecutions`, `ActiveSteps`, `ErrorMessage`\n- `ContainerID`, `ContainerKept`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`\n\n### 4. Server-Side Implementation (gRPC)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\nThe `GetStatus` method (lines 424-476):\n- Retrieves run from store\n- Checks container liveness via `container.Inspect()`\n- Loads step executions from captures store if available\n- Returns detailed status with timestamps\n\nContainer liveness check:\n```go\nif cs, err := s.container.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID); err == nil {\n    resp.ContainerAlive = cs.Running\n    if !cs.Running && !cs.FinishedAt.IsZero() {\n        resp.ContainerDeadSince = cs.FinishedAt.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Existing Tests\n**Files checked:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help_test.go` - Verifies help text exists for poll\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go` - Tests for server implementation\n- No direct unit tests for `cmdPoll` itself (integration testing pattern used)\n\nTest patterns observed:\n- Help text validation tests\n- Server round-trip tests with mock stores\n- Environment variable tests (using `t.Setenv()`)\n\n### 6. Multi-Argument Command Patterns\n**Reference implementations:**\n\n**Simple positional argument (like `poll`):**\n```go\n// status, stop, delete, poll - all single positional arg\nif len(args) < 1 {\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche status <run-id>\\n\")\n    os.Exit(1)\n}\nrunID := args[0]\n```\n\n**Flag-based arguments (`run`, `list`, `logs`):**\n```go\n// Iterate through args, matching flags and consuming next arg\nfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    switch args[i] {\n    case \"--workflow\":\n        if i+1 < len(args) {\n            i++\n            workflow = args[i]\n        }\n    case \"--prompt\", \"-p\":\n        if i+1 < len(args) {\n            i++\n            prompt = args[i]\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Mixed positional + flags (`workflow`):**\n```go\n// Extract first non-flag positional as workflow name\nfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    switch args[i] {\n    case \"--project\", \"-p\":\n        // flag handling\n    default:\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(args[i], \"-\") && workflowName == \"\" {\n            workflowName = args[i]\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Optional flag handling (`project`):**\n```go\n// Flag-only command with fallback to cwd\nvar name string\nfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    switch args[i] {\n    case \"--name\":\n        if i+1 < len(args) {\n            i++\n            name = args[i]\n        }\n    }\n}\nif name != \"\" {\n    req.Name = name\n} else {\n    cwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n    req.ProjectDir = cwd\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Help Text\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 85-95)\n\n```\ncloche poll — Wait for a run to finish\n\nPolls the daemon every 2 seconds and prints step-level progress until the\nrun reaches a terminal state (succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n\nUsage:\n  cloche poll <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nExit codes:\n  0    Run succeeded.\n  1    Run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche poll abc123\n  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n```\n\n### Key Implementation Details:\n\n1. **Polling Loop:** Infinite loop with 2-second sleep between checks\n2. **Change Detection:** Tracks `lastStepCount` and `lastState` to only print changes\n3. **Output Format:** `[HH:MM:SS] <event message>`\n4. **Container Death Detection:** Monitors `container_dead_since` timestamp, fails if >1 minute\n5. **Terminal State Detection:** Explicit checks for \"succeeded\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n6. **Error Handling:** Prints errors to stderr, exits with code 1 on failure\n7. **Step Event Printing:** Shows when steps start (empty Result) and complete (with Result)\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 128-129 for poll registration)\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 424-476 for GetStatus)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 85-95 for help text)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help_test.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad4f8e890b63d3fce (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63502\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 41418</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac30b052-9a54-423a-a143-d93519242f61","uuid":"2548b63f-aad9-4258-abb0-103373419758","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand the `cloche poll` command implementation. Find:\n1. The CLI command definition for `poll` (likely in cmd/cloche/)\n2. The gRPC service/client used for polling runs\n3. The domain types for Run status (terminal states, etc.)\n4. Any existing tests for the poll command\n5. How other multi-argument commands work in the CLI (for pattern reference)\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely.","agentId":"ad4f8e890b63d3fce","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Poll Command Implementation Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete understanding of the `cloche poll` command implementation:\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`\n\nThe `cmdPoll` function:\n- Takes a single required argument: `<run-id>`\n- Polls the daemon every 2 seconds indefinitely\n- Prints timestamped progress updates as steps start/complete\n- Monitors container liveness and detects container death after 1 minute\n- Exits with code 0 on success, 1 on failure/cancellation/container death\n- Checks for terminal states: `\"succeeded\"`, `\"failed\"`, `\"cancelled\"`\n- Tracks state changes and new step events to avoid duplicate output\n\nKey variables:\n```go\n- pollInterval := 2 * time.Second\n- containerDeadThreshold := 1 * time.Minute\n- lastStepCount, lastState (for change detection)\n```\n\n### 2. gRPC Service Interface\n**Files:** \n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n\nThe `poll` command uses `GetStatus` RPC:\n- Request: `GetStatusRequest` with `run_id` field\n- Response: `GetStatusResponse` containing:\n  - `run_id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `current_step`\n  - `step_executions` (array of `StepExecutionStatus`)\n  - `error_message`, `container_id`, `container_alive`, `container_dead_since`\n  - `title`, `is_host`\n\n### 3. Domain Types for Run Status\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\nRun state constants:\n```go\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\nTerminal states are: `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\nThe `Run` type includes:\n- `State`, `StepExecutions`, `ActiveSteps`, `ErrorMessage`\n- `ContainerID`, `ContainerKept`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`\n\n### 4. Server-Side Implementation (gRPC)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\nThe `GetStatus` method (lines 424-476):\n- Retrieves run from store\n- Checks container liveness via `container.Inspect()`\n- Loads step executions from captures store if available\n- Returns detailed status with timestamps\n\nContainer liveness check:\n```go\nif cs, err := s.container.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID); err == nil {\n    resp.ContainerAlive = cs.Running\n    if !cs.Running && !cs.FinishedAt.IsZero() {\n        resp.ContainerDeadSince = cs.FinishedAt.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Existing Tests\n**Files checked:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help_test.go` - Verifies help text exists for poll\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go` - Tests for server implementation\n- No direct unit tests for `cmdPoll` itself (integration testing pattern used)\n\nTest patterns observed:\n- Help text validation tests\n- Server round-trip tests with mock stores\n- Environment variable tests (using `t.Setenv()`)\n\n### 6. Multi-Argument Command Patterns\n**Reference implementations:**\n\n**Simple positional argument (like `poll`):**\n```go\n// status, stop, delete, poll - all single positional arg\nif len(args) < 1 {\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche status <run-id>\\n\")\n    os.Exit(1)\n}\nrunID := args[0]\n```\n\n**Flag-based arguments (`run`, `list`, `logs`):**\n```go\n// Iterate through args, matching flags and consuming next arg\nfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    switch args[i] {\n    case \"--workflow\":\n        if i+1 < len(args) {\n            i++\n            workflow = args[i]\n        }\n    case \"--prompt\", \"-p\":\n        if i+1 < len(args) {\n            i++\n            prompt = args[i]\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Mixed positional + flags (`workflow`):**\n```go\n// Extract first non-flag positional as workflow name\nfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    switch args[i] {\n    case \"--project\", \"-p\":\n        // flag handling\n    default:\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(args[i], \"-\") && workflowName == \"\" {\n            workflowName = args[i]\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Optional flag handling (`project`):**\n```go\n// Flag-only command with fallback to cwd\nvar name string\nfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    switch args[i] {\n    case \"--name\":\n        if i+1 < len(args) {\n            i++\n            name = args[i]\n        }\n    }\n}\nif name != \"\" {\n    req.Name = name\n} else {\n    cwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n    req.ProjectDir = cwd\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Help Text\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 85-95)\n\n```\ncloche poll — Wait for a run to finish\n\nPolls the daemon every 2 seconds and prints step-level progress until the\nrun reaches a terminal state (succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n\nUsage:\n  cloche poll <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nExit codes:\n  0    Run succeeded.\n  1    Run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche poll abc123\n  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n```\n\n### Key Implementation Details:\n\n1. **Polling Loop:** Infinite loop with 2-second sleep between checks\n2. **Change Detection:** Tracks `lastStepCount` and `lastState` to only print changes\n3. **Output Format:** `[HH:MM:SS] <event message>`\n4. **Container Death Detection:** Monitors `container_dead_since` timestamp, fails if >1 minute\n5. **Terminal State Detection:** Explicit checks for \"succeeded\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n6. **Error Handling:** Prints errors to stderr, exits with code 1 on failure\n7. **Step Event Printing:** Shows when steps start (empty Result) and complete (with Result)\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 128-129 for poll registration)\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 424-476 for GetStatus)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 85-95 for help text)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help_test.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":41418,"totalTokens":63502,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":495,"cache_read_inp